A NASA Parliamentaty Group meeting has resolved to recall Malindi MP Aisha Jumwa as its representative to the Parliamentary Service Commision. She will be replaced by Likoni MP Mishi Mboko. The minority side also removed Kiminini MP Chris Wamalwa as Minority Deputy Whip. Ford Kenya secretary general Eseli Simiyu replaces Wamalwa in the new changes announced by Minority Whip Junet Mohamed. "Party position and privileges must all times serve the party," Junet said on Thursday. Wamalwa is fighting accusations of loyalty to Deputy President William Ruto and has lost the confidence of opposition coalition National Super Alliance. In 2018, Ford Kenya Party leader and Bungoma Senator Moses Wetangula was replaced as Senate Minority leader, triggering a falling-out in the coalition. More follows...